							</svg>
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-4 text-gray-600">Gastric sleeve removes 80% of the stomach, while gastric bypass creates a small pouch and reroutes the intestine. Bypass typically leads to more weight loss and is better for diabetes, but has longer recovery. Sleeve is less complex with faster recovery. Your surgeon will recommend the best option for your needs.</p>
